22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65693bb086933e8fdb2eab1c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGeoffroy's%20depiction%20of%20the%20Nile%20crocodile%20(Crocodylus%20niloticus)%20from%20the%20Description%20de%20l'Egypte.%3Cp%3EDe%20Agostini%20Editorial%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEtienne%20Geoffroy%20Saint-Hilaire%20was%20convinced%20there%20were%20two%20species%20of%20crocodiles%20in%20the%20Nile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20Savigny%2C%20Geoffroy%20was%20a%20prolific%20collector.%20While%20in%20Egypt%2C%20he%20studied%20bats%2C%20mongooses%2C%20tortoises%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20Geoffroy%20was%20able%20to%20dissect%20and%20stuff%20so%20many%20specimens%20was%20he%20had%20purchased%20an%2011-year-old%20enslaved%20boy%2C%20whom%20he%20trained%20to%20help%20with%20his%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeoffroy%20closely%20examined%20so%20many%20different%20kinds%20of%20animals%20that%20he%20started%20to%20see%20patterns%20between%20even%20very%20different%20species.%20It%20led%20to%20his%20theory%20of%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0160932707000804%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eunity%20of%20plan%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bunity%20of%20composition%26quot%3B%20a%20kind%20of%20quasi-evolutionary%20idea%20that%20Charles%20Darwin%20would%20reference%20decades%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeoffroy's%20theories%20often%20irritated%20his%20fellow%20naturalists.%20That%20includes%20when%20he%20attempted%20to%20demonstrate%20a%20mummified%20crocodile%20he'd%20taken%20from%20Egypt%20represented%20a%20separate%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20jaw%20was%20completely%20different%20from%20the%20Nile%20crocodile%2C%20Geoffroy%20said.%20Plus%2C%20it%20was%20less%20aggressive.%20One%20had%20even%20been%20on%20display%20in%20Paris.%20%26quot%3BIt%20took%20pleasure%20in%20being%20patted%3B%20and%20anyone%20might%2C%20without%20the%20least%20danger%2C%20open%20its%20mouth%2C%20and%20place%20his%20hand%20between%20its%20teeth%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fbooks%2Fedition%2FNew_Monthly_Magazine_and_Humorist%2FR8g2AQAAMAAJ%3Fhl%3Den%26gbpv%3D1%26dq%3DGeoffroy%2BSaint-Hilaire%2Bcrocodile%2Bsuchus%26pg%3DPA158%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%23v%3Donepage%26q%3DGeoffroy%2520Saint-Hilaire%2520crocodile%2520suchus%26f%3Dfalse%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eaccording%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20one%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20colleagues%20didn't%20believe%20him.%20However%2C%20over%20200%20years%20later%2C%20biologist%20Evon%20Hekkala%20and%20a%20team%20of%20researchers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.fordham.edu%2Fscience%2Fnew-croc-discovered-by-fordham-biologist%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eanalyzed%20the%20DNA%20of%20modern%20crocodiles%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20some%20of%20Geoffroy's%20mummies%20to%20confirm%20his%20suspicions.%20Indeed%2C%20they%20showed%20two%20separate%20species%20swam%20in%20the%20Nile%3A%20Crocodylus%20niloticus%20and%20Crocodylus%20suchus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E5.%20The%20advent%20of%20ophthalmology%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222114%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20engraving%20of%20the%20house%20of%20Osman%20Bey%20with%20elaborate%20columns%2C%20several%20levels%2C%20a%20brick%20wall%2C%20and%20people%20and%20a%20camel%20and%20horses%20in%20the%20courtyard%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6569373186933e8fdb2eaabb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20engraving%20from%20the%20Description%20de%20l'Egypte%20showing%20the%20interior%20courtyard%20of%20a%20house.%3Cp%3EScience%20%26amp%3B%20Society%20Picture%20Library%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20French%20physicians%20who%20accompanied%20Napoleon%20encountered%20unfamiliar%20illnesses%20in%20Egpyt.%20One%20disease%20that%20traveled%20with%20them%20back%20to%20Europe%20was%20something%20they%20called%20Egyptian%20ophthalmia.%20Now%20known%20as%20trachoma%2C%20it%20can%20cause%20itchy%2C%20swollen%20eyes%20and%20lead%20to%20blindness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20became%20so%20prevalent%20that%20physicians%20all%20over%20Europe%20started%20studying%20the%20disease.%20Geoffroy%2C%20who%20contracted%20it%2C%20was%20%26quot%3Btotally%20blind%26quot%3B%20for%20weeks%3Cu%3E%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0160932707000804%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20wrote%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUp%20to%20that%20point%2C%20ophthalmology%20wasn't%20a%20formalized%20branch%20of%20scientific%20research%2C%20but%20the%20race%20to%20find%20the%20origin%20of%20this%20disease%20laid%20the%20groundwork%20for%20its%20creation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20British%20physician%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F6359513%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EJohn%20Vetch%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20realized%20the%20pus%20from%20an%20infected%20eye%20could%20spread%20the%20disease.%20Knowing%20it%20was%20contagious%2C%20Vetch%20developed%20methods%20of%20prevention%20and%20treatment%20that%20are%20considered%20milestones%20in%20the%20history%20of%20ophthalmology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E6.%20The%20Rosetta%20Stone%20helped%20Champollion%20decipher%20hieroglyphs%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221914%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20and%20woman%20in%201930s%20clothing%20stand%20in%20front%20of%20and%20behind%20the%20Rosetta%20Stone%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65693d0b86933e8fdb2eab3a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Rosetta%20Stone%20is%20housed%20at%20the%20British%20Museum.%3Cp%3EFox%20Photos%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20centuries%2C%20no%20one%20could%20read%20hieroglyphs%2C%20the%20pictorial%20writing%20that%20covered%20many%20Egyptian%20monuments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnine-archaeology-discoveries-changed-understanding-human-history-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFrench%20found%20the%20Rosetta%20Stone%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20their%20invasion%2C%20they%20knew%20it%20could%20serve%20as%20a%20kind%20of%20translation%20key.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeciphering%20hieroglyphs%20would%20allow%20scholars%20to%20read%20the%20writing%20on%20scores%20of%20other%20Ancient%20Egyptian%20texts%20and%20monuments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201801%2C%20the%20British%20were%20negotiating%20for%20France's%20surrender.%20One%20stipulation%20was%20that%20the%20British%20would%20take%20the%20antiquities%20and%20the%20savants'%20collections%2C%20which%20included%20the%20Rosetta%20Stone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeoffroy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fbooks%2Fedition%2FMirage%2Fn--z6iyUooUC%3Fhl%3Den%26gbpv%3D1%26dq%3Dmirage%2Bnapoleon%2527s%2Bscientists%2Band%2Bthe%2Bunveiling%2Bof%2Begypt%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20the%20British%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20savants%20would%20%26quot%3Bdestroy%20our%20property%2C%20we%20will%20disperse%20it%20in%20the%20Libyan%20sands%2C%20or%20we%20will%20throw%20it%20into%20the%20sea%26quot%3B%20before%20they%20handed%20it%20over.%20They%20were%20allowed%20to%20keep%20their%20notes%20and%20collections.%20But%20not%20the%20slab.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20texts%20were%20inscribed%20on%20the%20stone%20in%20Egyptian%20hieroglyphs%2C%20an%20Egyptian%20cursive%20script%20derived%20from%20hieroglyphs%2C%20and%20Ancient%20Greek.%20Since%20the%20three%20were%20identical%2C%20the%20Greek%20writing%20could%20help%20researchers%20decipher%20the%20hieroglyphs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20two%20decades%20for%20French%20scholar%20Jean-Fran%C3%A7ois%20Champollion%20to%20translate%20them.%20Champollion%20made%20use%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnapoleon.lindahall.org%2Frosetta_stone.shtml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecopy%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20French%20savants%20had%20taken%20of%20the%20slab%20and%20published.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Rosetta%20Stone%20is%20currently%20in%20the%20British%20Museum.%20Egypt%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fancient-artifacts-countries-are-still-fighting-over-history-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrying%20to%20get%20it%20back%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bspoil%20of%20war.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E7.%20The%20invention%20of%20an%20engraving%20machine%20that%20sped%20up%20the%20printing%20process%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222115%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20drawing%20of%20a%20domed%20mosque%20and%20tall%20tower%20in%20Cairo%20circa%201798%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65693ed947f9ecb37d88f3ed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJust%20one%20of%20the%20many%20detailed%20engravings%20added%20to%20the%20Description%20de%20l'Egypte%2C%20this%20one%20of%20a%20mosque%20in%20Cairo.%3Cp%3EScience%20%26amp%3B%20Society%20Picture%20Library%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20savants%20returned%20to%20France%2C%20many%20worked%20on%20compiling%20the%20multi-volume%20book%20%26quot%3BDescription%20de%20l'E%CC%81gypte%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20amounted%20to%207%2C000%20pages%20encompassing%20what%20they'd%20seen%20and%20studied%20in%20Egypt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20save%20some%20of%20the%20laborious%20work%20of%20engraving%2C%20engineer%20Nicolas-Jacques%20Cont%C3%A9%20created%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnapoleon.lindahall.org%2Fengraving.shtml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emachine%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20automated%20part%20of%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20print%20the%20hundreds%20of%20illustrations%2C%20engravers%20first%20had%20to%20transfer%20them%20to%20copper%20plates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20plates%20with%20monuments%2C%20Cont%C3%A9's%20machine%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.archaeology.org%2F9905%2Fabstracts%2Fegypt.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eengrave%20the%20sky%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20background.%20The%20engraver%20could%20program%20it%20to%20create%20clouds%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20originally%20would've%20taken%20six%20to%20eight%20months%20could%20be%20completed%20in%20just%20a%20few%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20still%20a%20massive%20undertaking%20and%20considered%20to%20be%20the%20most%20ambitious%20work%20of%20France%20in%20the%20early%2019th%20Century.%20The%20first%20volume%20wasn't%20printed%20until%201809.%20The%20final%20volume%20came%20out%20in%20the%20late%201820s%2C%20nearly%20a%20decade%20after%20Napoloen's%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E8.%20The%20science%20of%20geology%20flourished%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226045%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Drawings%20of%20Fossil%20shells%20found%20in%20Egypt%20printed%20in%201817%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F673615f6fa0140cdd5636548%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223423%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFossil%20shells%20found%20by%20Fran%C3%A7ois-Michel%20de%20Rozi%C3%A8re%20from%20Description%20de%20l'Egypte.%3Cp%3EDe%20Agostini%20Editorial%2FICAS94%2FContributor%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20savants%20were%20tasked%20with%20documenting%20the%20natural%20history%20of%20Egypt.%20Mining%20engineer%20Fran%C3%A7ois-Michel%20de%20Rozi%C3%A8re%20had%20the%20difficult%20job%20of%20describing%20the%20country's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frare-earth-elements-minerals-brook-mine-wyoming-ramaco-atkins-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erocks%20and%20minerals%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDecades%20before%20Napoleon's%20invasion%2C%20many%20naturalists%20started%20adopting%20Carl%20Linnaeus'%20two-word%20system%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcelebrity-species-named-eponyms-nomenclature-taxonomy%23david-bowie-and-the-heteropoda-davidbowie-spider-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enaming%20plants%20and%20animals%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20rocks%20and%20minerals%20lacked%20a%20similar%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnapoleon.lindahall.org%2Fminerals_of_egypt.shtml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewidely%20accepted%3C%2Fa%3E%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20accurately%20capture%20the%20nuances%20of%20the%20granite%20or%20shells%20he%20saw%2C%20Rozi%C3%A8re%20painstakingly%20described%20their%20textures%2C%20layers%2C%20and%20colors.%20One%20description%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F986871%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereferenced%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Btransparent%20quartz%2C%20yellowish%20feldspath%2C%20and%20black%20schist.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20understood%20the%20importance%20of%20including%20illustrations%20of%20the%20rocks%2C%20which%20made%20them%20much%20easier%20for%20other%20savants%20to%20identify.%20In%20the%20Description%20de%20l'Egypte%2C%20his%20fifteen%20plates%20contained%20over%20100%20colorful%20illustrations%20of%20porphyry%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscientists-pilot-project-inject-carbon-into-ocean-floor-holes-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebasalt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20other%20rocks%20and%20fossils.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Napoleon%20didn't%20use%20the%20geological%20knowledge%20his%20savants%20gathered%20in%20Egypt%2C%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lyellcollection.org%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1144%2Fsp473.15%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eargue%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20his%20invasion%20spurred%20the%20creation%20of%20military%20geology.%20Soon%2C%20scientists%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usgs.gov%2Fpublications%2Freports-and-maps-military-geology-unit-1942-1975%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurveying%3C%2Fa%3E%20unfamiliar%20terrain%20during%20campaigns%20and%20using%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.geolsoc.org.uk%2F2018%2F11%2F09%2Fmilitary-geology-an-innovation-of-the-1914-18-world-war%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eknowledge%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20engineering%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E9.%20An%20attempt%20to%20date%20Egyptian%20antiquity%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224307%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20circular%20part%20of%20a%20ceiling%20with%20zodiac%20symbols%20carved%20into%20it%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6744e195fa0140cdd5654fbf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223796%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Dendera%20zodiac%20is%20currently%20in%20the%20Louvre.%3Cp%3EJOSEPH%20EID%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20midst%20of%20his%20work%20on%20the%20Rosetta%20Stone%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpress.princeton.edu%2Fbooks%2Fhardcover%2F9780691200903%2Fthe-riddle-of-the-rosetta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChampollion%3C%2Fa%3E%20decried%20the%20removal%20of%20another%20piece%20of%20Ancient%20Egyptian%20history%20from%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20quick%20visit%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-worlds-first-travel-photographs-are-up-for-auction-and-they-offer-an-unprecedented-glimpse-into-ancient-egypt-2016-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Dendera%20temple%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Denon%20had%20sketched%20the%20ceiling%2C%20where%20Ancient%20Egyptians%20had%20carved%20zodiac%20signs%2C%20Egyptian%20constellations%2C%20and%20other%20figures%20into%20the%20stone.%20Other%20engineers%20made%20more%20detailed%20drawings%20of%20the%20intricate%20design.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20hre